"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code is incorrectly using Matplotlib's date-related functions. Specifically, the `MonthLocator` and `DateFormatter` are being used, but the x-axis values are not being converted to matplotlib's date format using `date2num`. This will cause the dates to not be displayed correctly on the x-axis.\",\n  \"patch\": \"17c17\\n<ax.set_xticks(df.date.unique())\\n---\\n>import matplotlib.dates as mdates\\n>date_nums = mdates.date2num(df.date.unique())\\n>ax.set_xticks(date_nums)\\n\"\n}"